OL,6,FIt found that despite rising female
OL,7,Fparticipation rates in Ireland, a
OL,8,Fsignificant gender income gap
OL,9,Fpersists, primarily driven by lower
OL,10,Ffemale participation rates and a
OL,11,Fhigher incidence of part-time
OL,12,Femployment.
OL,14,FIt said that the gap often starts
OL,15,Fafter the birth of a child and
OL,16,Fcontinues throughout a woman's
OL,17,Flifetime.
