OL,4,Cpaternity leave ` report
OL,6,FUsing a 10% sample of all births
OL,7,Fbetween 2019 and 2022, the report
OL,8,Fanalyses the characteristics linked
OL,9,Fwith the take-up of paternity and
OL,10,Fparent's benefit, as well as the
OL,11,Fduration of paid and unpaid maternity
OL,12,Fleave.
OL,14,FThe findings reveal that higher paid
OL,15,Ffathers, who are more likely to
OL,16,Freceive employer top-ups, were more
OL,17,Flikely to avail of paternity leave.
