OL,6,FLiam Herrick, chief commissioner of
OL,7,Fthe Irish Human Rights and Equality
OL,8,FCommission, said: "The fact that women
OL,9,Fdo far more care and care work, paid
OL,10,Fand unpaid, than men plays a
OL,11,Fsignificant part in women's lower
OL,12,Feconomic status in Ireland.
OL,14,F"To address persistent, structural
OL,15,Finequality between women and men,
OL,16,FIreland must find a new relationship
OL,17,Fbetween paid employment, care work and
OL,18,Fgender roles.
